Description: CVE-2026-5704 - Fix -t/-x discrepancies enabling hidden file injection
 The -t (list) and -x (extract) operations disagree about archive member
 boundaries, enabling injection of hidden files with attacker-controlled
 content bypassing pre-extraction inspection. This patch centralizes
 skip_member handling in extract_archive, fixes read_header LNKTYPE size
 handling, and properly tracks the skipped state.
Origin: upstream, https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/tar.git/commit/?id=b8d8a61b25588caca4efaf9bdd2e3f1a49da77e3
Author: Paul Eggert <eggert@cs.ucla.edu>
Last-Update: 2026-03-22

